### Map Basics

A Map is an unordered collection of key-value pairs. Keys must be unique.

```dart
void main() {
  // Creating maps
  Map<String, int> ages = {
    'Alice': 30,
    'Bob': 25,
    'Charlie': 35,
  };

  var empty = <String, int>{};

  // Accessing values
  print(ages['Alice']); // 30
  print(ages['David']); // null (key not found)

  // Adding and updating
  ages['David'] = 28;  // Add new
  ages['Alice'] = 31;  // Update existing

  print(ages.length); // 4
}
```

### Map Methods

| Method | Description | Example |
|--------|-------------|---------|
| `containsKey(key)` | Checks for key | `map.containsKey('a')` |
| `containsValue(val)` | Checks for value | `map.containsValue(10)` |
| `putIfAbsent(key, fn)` | Adds if absent | `map.putIfAbsent('a', () => 1)` |
| `remove(key)` | Removes entry | `map.remove('a')` |
| `clear()` | Removes all | `map.clear()` |
| `addAll(otherMap)` | Adds all pairs | `map.addAll({'b': 2})` |
| `update(key, fn)` | Updates existing | `map.update('a', (v) => v + 1)` |

### Iterating Over Maps

```dart
void main() {
  var scores = {'Alice': 95, 'Bob': 87, 'Charlie': 92};

  // Iterate over entries
  for (var entry in scores.entries) {
    print('${entry.key}: ${entry.value}');
  }

  // Iterate over keys
  for (var name in scores.keys) {
    print('Name: $name');
  }

  // Iterate over values
  for (var score in scores.values) {
    print('Score: $score');
  }

  // Using forEach
  scores.forEach((name, score) {
    print('$name scored $score');
  });
}
```

### Map Properties

```dart
void main() {
  var map = {'a': 1, 'b': 2, 'c': 3};

  print(map.length);    // 3
  print(map.isEmpty);   // false
  print(map.isNotEmpty); // true
  print(map.keys);      // (a, b, c)
  print(map.values);    // (1, 2, 3)
  print(map.entries);   // (MapEntry(a: 1), ...)
}
```

### Nested Maps

```dart
void main() {
  var users = {
    'alice': {'age': 30, 'email': 'alice@example.com'},
    'bob': {'age': 25, 'email': 'bob@example.com'},
  };

  print(users['alice']?['email']); // alice@example.com
}
```

> **Key Point:** Accessing a non-existent key returns `null`. Use `putIfAbsent()` to lazily add missing entries. Use `entries` property for iteration.

